# config/unbound.records.example
# Example records for a VCF-like environment
#
# Built-in Provider Box service records (DNS, CA, Keycloak, NetBox, S3, SFTP, Syslog)
# are generated automatically from config/provider-box.env and must NOT be added here.
#
# Use this file only for external/custom records that should be published by Unbound
# and optionally imported into NetBox.
#
# Format:
# <fqdn> <ip>
# <fqdn> <ip/cidr>
#
# If you specify <ip/cidr>, Provider Box can derive the surrounding subnet
# and seed a NetBox prefix object in addition to an IP address object using
# the same subnet mask.
#
# If you specify only <ip>, Provider Box imports the host IP as /32 and does
# not guess the subnet. This avoids incorrect prefix assumptions for mixed
# networks.
#
# PTR records are generated automatically by the bootstrap script

host32.sddc.lab 10.203.5.32/24
pod-240-vc01.sddc.lab 10.203.240.10/24
pod-240-nsx.sddc.lab 10.203.240.11/24
pod-240-nsx1.sddc.lab 10.203.240.12/24
